Endpoints.Name: Create and update LOS (Length of Stay) pricing
Endpoints.Description:
Introduction: You can use this function if you would like to send BookingPal different prices for various Length of Stays with the same starting date.

LOS Pricing will be a different method in sending rates to BookingPal and is defined as pricing sent for a specific âStay rangesâ, In the LOS  method you are setting specific rates based on the Length of Stay. (This is a different way to push rates to BookingPal. )

For date periods of 1 to 30 days a specific rate need to enter check-in date and a rate for every possible reservation starting at that date (i.e. 1 day, 2 days, up to 30 days, 30 days is the maximum value allowed for this field) you will need to send BookingPal total rate value for that period. 

Maximum LOS number of days is 30. All other LOS values after 30 will not be saved. If you do not support reservation for some specific number of dates - send value 0.00 for this LOS number of days. Keep in mind that all values not sent for any specific check-in date will be considered as 0, and reservation for this number of days will not be possible.
Field maxGuests allows you to set different rates per different number of guests. If you do not have different rate values per number of guests - you can send the value for maximum number of guests, and all others will have the same rate.

For MLT properties which supported LOS price for update number of count you can use it rates and availability API.

It is suggested to manage availability over ârates and availabilityâ API call, and to close/open dates over this call.

Note: this API call can be used only if you set supportedLosRates = true on the product. Otherwise using this API for specific product is not possible.

This function allows the logged-in user to add yield management rules for the specific product. Yield management rules can affect the final price of the property depending on some special conditions (like the length of stay, early booking, etc.). These rules automate price manipulations, on an inquiry by inquiry basis. When set criteria are met, they help maximize revenue and occupancy.

How is the price calculated?
The price for a night is calculated based on the basic price and the yield management rules.

- If no YMR:
{basic price per night} = price per night
- If YMR is set it can Increase/decrease percent or increase/decrease amount:
	{basic price per night} + {yield amount} = {price per night}
	or
	{basic price per night} - {yield amount} = {price per night}

The below examples will use the scenario to walk you step by step and explain how the price is calculated based on different YMRs. 
Letâs say that the basic price per night for 2016 is 100 USD.

This function is used also for updating yield. So if you already create a specific yield for some date - and you send a new one - we will update the yield for this date.
If you need to delete a specific yield type - you can send an empty list for that type.

EndpointGroups.Name: Request To Book
EndpointGroups.Description: Some channels like Airbnb have an option for guests to use the âRequest to bookâ possibility, where the Property Manager needs to approve or decline the booking within the next 24 hours. If the period expires - the booking will be automatically cancelled by Airbnb. Once this booking request is received from the channel side, it will be forwarded to the PMS over this API by sending a notification to the ârequestToBook'' link, which can be set through the Push notification API. Corresponding dates will not be closed at that point in time and should be kept open. Thereâs a 24 hour window to either accept or avoid the reservation. If this reservation is avoided, it will be cancelled in both the mybookingpal system and on the channel. If the reservation is accepted, that information will be sent to the channel where a new reservation will be created, and then subsequent information sent back over regular New reservation notification flow. Bear in mind that once the requests to book are received (and more importantly, once they are accepted) â dates must remain open in your system, otherwise a real reservation creation will not be possible.

Fields.Description: Language 2 letter value  as ISO 639-1 code

Fields.Description: Email of PM. Email need to be unique in BP system, so you might receive error if we already have this email in our system

Fields.Description: Country code prefix in phone number. For example â+1â.

Fields.Description: Full URL to PM terms and conditions

Fields.Name: leadTime
Fields.Description: Minimum number of days before check-in for which reservation is allowed to be booked. Allowed values are 0-7.

Fields.Name: type
Fields.Description: Full or Split payment. In case of Split payment - it will be 2 payments. {SPLIT, FULL}

Fields.Name: splitPayment
Fields.Description: Model. Required only if SPLIT type is selected.

Fields.Name: secondPaymentDays
Fields.Description: Number of days before check-in when second payment is required.

Fields.Name: manualPolicy
Fields.Description: Model. Mandatory only if MANUAL type is chosen.

Fields.Name: chargeValue
Fields.Description: Percentage or flat value which will be charged in case of cancellation

Fields.Name: beforeDays
Fields.Description: Days before check-in when cancellation policy will be charged

Fields.Name: cancellationFee
Fields.Description: Cancellation transaction fee - additional fee on cancellation

Fields.Name: isFeeMandatory
Fields.Description: Used in BookingPal validator. Info does property require any fee or not. Default value is TRUE. This setup can be overridden on property level with different API call, which is stronger.

Fields.Name: isTaxMandatory
Fields.Description: Used in BookingPal validator. Info does property require any tax or not. Default value is TRUE. This setup can be overridden on property level with different API call, which is stronger.

Fields.Name: paymentType
Fields.Description: Type how payment will be processed. {CREDIT_CARD,MAIL_CHECK,BOOKING_PAL_MOR}

Fields.Name: creditCard
Fields.Description: Model. Mandatory if CREDIT_CARD type is selected.

Fields.Name: creditCardType
Fields.Description: Type of payment - will payment be processed over API (in reservation request - transmit), or will payment be processed over payment gateway (post). {TRANSMIT,POST}

Fields.Name: paymentGateways
Fields.Description: Model. Mandatory if POST type is selected

Fields.Name: creditCardList
Fields.Description: List of acceptable credit cards. Allowed only if type is TRANSMIT. {MASTER_CARD,VISA,AMERICAN_EXPRESS,DINERS_CLUB,DISCOVER}. If POST method selected it will select all creditCardList.

Fields.Name: user
Fields.Description: Value necessary for accessing payment gateway, values are different per payment gateway: PAYPAL - Client ID AUTHORIZE_NET - User ID BRIDGE_PAY - Username PAY_BOX - Site number DIBS - Login O_GONE - User ID DOC_DATA - ID PAY_GATE - ID  Note: This value will not be returned in response.

Fields.Name: secret
Fields.Description: Value necessary for accessing payment gateway, values are different per payment gateway: PAYPAL - Secret AUTHORIZE_NET - Transaction Key BRIDGE_PAY - Password  PAY_BOX - Rank number DIBS - Password O_GONE - Password  DOC_DATA - Password PAY_GATE - Password  Note: This value will not be returned in response.

Fields.Name: additionalField1
Fields.Description: Additional value necessary for accessing some payment gateways, values are different per payment gateway: BRIDGE_PAY - Merchant Number PAY_BOX - An identifier DIBS - Merchant ID O_GONE - PSP ID  Note: This value will not be returned in response.

Fields.Name: additionalField2
Fields.Description: Additional value necessary for accessing some payment gateways, values are different per payment gateway: BRIDGE_PAY - Merchant Number PAY_BOX - An identifier DIBS - Merchant ID O_GONE - PSP ID  Note: This value will not be returned in response.

Fields.Name: altId
Fields.Description: Alternative Id of the property (ID in your PMS system).   Note: this field you can not update, so this field will not be used during update.

Fields.Name: supplierId
Fields.Description: Id of the Property Manager (not be used for creating new property. Property will have ID of current authorized user)

Fields.Name: rooms
Fields.Description: Number of bedrooms. Number of bedrooms should be > 0. Value 0 is only allowed in case property type  is Studio (PCT46 or PCT110)

Fields.Name: spaceUnit
Fields.Description: {SQ_M, SQ_FT} Property size unit of measurement

Fields.Name: childs
Fields.Description: Number of allowed children (from 7 to 12 years)

Fields.Name: latitude
Fields.Description: Latitude of the property (Must set field latitude and longitude or location)

Fields.Name: longitude
Fields.Description: Longitude of the property (Must set field latitude and longitude or location)

Fields.Name: attributesWithQuantity
Fields.Description: Use this param instead of previous if you need to set quantity more than 1 of attributes. If use both in POST request this will overwrite the previous list (under param attributes).

Fields.Name: nearbyAmenities
Fields.Description: List of Nearby Attributes models. Check allowed values in Appendix.

Fields.Name: currency
Fields.Description: Property currency. ISO 4217 code is required.

Fields.Name: location
Fields.Description: Property location (Must set field latitude and longitude or location). Some location data will not be updated, since it is not expected that property change location. Similar is with coordinates and searching location from coordinates.

Fields.Name: supportedLosRates
Fields.Description: If true - means that the property supports only LOS rates. So daily rates can not be sent and updated. Default is false.

Fields.Name: touristLicenseExpiryDate
Fields.Description: Tourist license expiry date. Correct date format is YYYY-MM-DD.

Fields.Name: multiUnit
Fields.Description: For regular properties (single units) you should not use this field. This field is to set if you want to create multiunit property or owner {MLT,OWN}. Also you can not update this field.

Fields.Name: parentId
Fields.Description: This fields should not be used unless your property is not MLT (check field multiunit). In this case you must set owner (parent) id property to which this property will belong. Also you can not update this property.
